The paper discusses the use of wireless physical-layer identification (WPLI) techniques for wireless security solutions, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves theoretical modeling and experiment validation, which suggests that it could be categorized under information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, since the focus of the paper is on wireless security, cs.CR is the most likely category.
